…As Ndume Walks Tight Rope ABUJA – Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Borno State chapter, Ali Bukar Dalori, has declared the readiness of the state for the party’s special Convention to elect its presidential flagbearer on Sunday in Abuja Dalori disclosed in a telephone chat that the 81 delegates from the 27 Local Government Areas of the state have emerged and are poised to carry out the national assignment alongside other delegates, adding that the state is also ready for the Governorship primaries slated for the Maiduguri Sports Stadium. -Advertisement- He equally disclosed that the primary to nominate the Governorship flagbearer would not pose a challenge considering that the incumbent holder, Prof Babagana Umaru Zullum, is running unopposed. According to him, the governor is likely to emerge by the unanimous affirmation of the delegates on Thursday at an event slated for 10 am on Thursday. Alhaji Dalori also disclosed that arrangement has also been concluded for other primaries elections of the party, pointing out that two of the three Senators are running unopposed except for Borno Southern Senatorial district where Senator Ali Ndume is being challenged. Giving further insight into the race, APC Zonal Chairman Alhaji Aliyu Yerima disclosed that Senator Ndume is being challenged by Alh Idris Mamman Durkwa, Aliyu Mohd Lawan Buba Bamanga and Mohammed Musa Tumala. “We expect a keen contest,” he forecasted.